Amazon Alexa and the Vibe Lite products work together to help your control home appliances nice and easy.
You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off or dim the light. 
Now there’s no need to go to the switch to adjust/control your home lighting. Just ask Alexa (on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap or Echo Show) to do it; after connecting Alexa to your Vibe Lite products in a few simple steps:

(1). Download our "Vibe Lite" app in android or iOS app market;
(2). Register one Vibe Lite account in your "Vibe Lite" app;
(4). Configure your Vibe Lite devices in your "Vibe Lite" app and assign appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "Vibe Lite" skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android, ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "Vibe Lite" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "Vibe Lite", and you'll be navigated to Vibe Lite login page;
(9). Input your Vibe Lite account username and password, you'll be redirected to the success page;
(10). Now close the page and you can start controlling your Vibe Lite devices with Alexa. 

You can enjoy voice control on your home devices by saying something like these commands:
“Alexa, turn on kitchen light"
“Alexa, turn off kitchen light"
“Alexa, dim livingroom light"
“Alexa, brighten livingroom light"
“Alexa, set the livingroom light to 20 percent"
“Alexa, set bedroom light to Blue"
“Alexa, turn on bedroom air conditioner"
